<collectingCountry id="F33A1B96F779B138B234FBE431F44777" box="[881,973,1051,1077]" name="Sweden" pageId="12" pageNumber="533">Sweden</collectingCountry>
. 
<location id="8EF20DDDF779B138B29FFBE431D44777" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F779B138B1D2FC9836814433:8EF20DDDF779B138B29FFBE431D44777" box="[986,1005,1051,1077]" country="Sweden" county="Berlin" municipality="Okavango River" name="If" pageId="12" pageNumber="533">If</location>
there were more specimens available to 
<location id="8EF20DDDF779B138B1F0FBC0331D471B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F779B138B1D2FC9836814433:8EF20DDDF779B138B1F0FBC0331D471B" box="[181,292,1087,1113]" country="Sweden" county="Berlin" municipality="Okavango River" name="Wahlberg" pageId="12" pageNumber="533">Wahlberg</location>
, we assume they are lost. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F779B138B30BFBC031B4471B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[590,909,1087,1113]" pageId="12" pageNumber="533" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 39–40)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 568742 [11734] as a “type”, treated here as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F779B138B00AFB9C338F473F" box="[335,438,1123,1149]" pageId="12" pageNumber="533">lectotype</typeStatus>
